Gave myself a lil break but getting organized to dive head first back into quantum healing / past life hypnosis sessions by reviewing lovely feedback🥲 
A perspective that came up in a session this week I enjoyed was the reminder that you don't have to subscribe to the idea of a 'set norm' daily routine or even career if it doesn't suit you. 
The client's higher self used a simple analogy to explain how they don't have to follow something that doesn't work for their personality 
"... even the concept of a 7 day week doesn't work for their mind, they don't have to stay in on mondays and tuesdays just because everyone else does - they can go for datenight on wednesday if they want!"
Although they're are aspects of living within the system that we are in that we generally all have to partake in, you can exercise your choice to reshape the box that isn't working for you into something better suited to you.
I also feel like it echoes this fun journey I'm on where I get to both use my practical and creative skills for work and to pay my bills and my human-to-human skills towards my life purpose work. I'm enjoying the little crossover in between, and the fact it doesn't have to make sense - it just has to work for me! ❤️

(I'll let you guys know when my schedule clears for bookings, ya girls gonna be kept busy for a while!😅)

As a previously convicted avoidant and master hermit life-liver I understand how this intuitive message for today might feel like an attack - I promise you it's not! 
Ofc there are situations in where removing yourself completely is necessary but if there are re-occurring patterns or projections creating negative experiences you would like to move past I invite you to dive deeper into the feeling. 
Understand the triggers will always be there, however what you do have much more power over is your a desire to reprogram your reaction to them (perhaps through a deep shift of perspective) to something more in alignment with how you prefer to feel.
This journey is forever a work in progress but the benefit of this type of self-growth is that you become a much more confidently active participant in the experience of life and its obstacles, instead of avoidant. Thoughts?❤️

CONTINUE READING⬇️
Forgiveness, let's talk about it! 
In all the travels to my internal world, reading, studying, talking to people, working with clients under hypnosis, and experiencing this for myself etc forgiveness is probably one of the biggest obstacles in the way of our healing, manifestations and peace. 

The abridged version of these findings and to explain my quote further is that forgiving a person, situation, trauma, guilt whatever it may be is one of the single hardest things a hurt human being can learn how to do. The hurt is so a part of your identity sometimes you don't know who you would be without it. 
However I've found that forgiveness is also one of the biggest acts of rebellion against what ever happened you could possibly take. 
I think we automatically think when we forgive something thats happened to us it means letting whatever caused the hurt off the hook, when in actuality holding on to a bitterness or a wrongdoing only keeps us locked in a loop with it.
So when I say forgiveness is for you, I truly mean it - because it's you that has to carry around the burden of it everyday.
Forgiveness can be carried out in private, on a soul level without the other person ever knowing or deciding to acknowledge an unfair past event and deciding to put it down to rest. You don't even have to believe your own words, but eventually your mind will follow yours words and you'll be able to move forward if you wish without carrying that extra weight in the way of what you deserve. 
Forgiveness is for you.

CONTINUE READING⬇️ Once you understand what projection is, it's almost impossible to take anything personally. Today's intuitive message is about how authentic living is a trigger for those who aren't quite comfortable with some aspect of themselves. I think it's quite an interesting observation since the side doing the projecting will most often not see that the issue lies within them or their expectations and that most personal opinions are derived from the perspective of our own self-concept and limiting beliefs.
As a simple example - do you really hate her outfit or do you just hate that she's able to express herself in a way that you can't without being embarrassed? 
Next time you feel yourself projecting an expectation, or a negative opinion maybe take a moment to ask yourself what part of yourself is projecting into that comment.
We all go through bouts of this, it's natural but I've found being self-aware of when it's happening is an opportunity to look within, correct behavior and get back to a secure state of being where you're too busy being yourself you become totally indifferent to what anyone else is doing 😌

In the spirit of the nostalgia that seems to have permeated the start of the month I thought I'd revisit one of my biggest learned lessons. 
As a recovering people pleaser, I recognize all of the times I made excuses for people when they would show me time and time again with their actions and hollow words that they simply did not respect me, even when they wanted to.

There was a time I'd read something like this and immediately go on the offense, in my mind defending my acceptance of disrespect I had allowed into my life. For those on the other side of that understanding, you'll feel the truth in it. Growing the and nurturing the respect you have for yourself starts with what you allow into your life. Relationships and friendships become very straightforward when you have a strict no-tolerance policy for disrespect (my general hot take/ overall approach to life, but ofc leave room for nuance!)

✨NOSARA, COSTA RICA FAVS LIST✨ more details below ⬇️ + bookmark for your future travel inspo!
1. Cacao Ceremony with Marypaz of @abundia_salud - when it comes to anything spiritual in any place you visit I would highly recommend going with people who are from the general region. The experience is so much richer this way and the ceremony was a beautiful mix of music, dance, connection and emotional release with this non psychedelic plant medicine.

2. Seasonal turtle activity and nesting happens multiple times a year at Ostional Wildlife Refuge and you can safely catch an turtle arribada with a guide from the refuge. You can whatsapp Asociación de Guías Locales de Ostional at +506 6252 7412 for reservations. If your into a David Attenborough moment this is it!

3. @sibu_wildlife_sanctuary was a wonderful way to learn about the local plant life & wildlife. The focus of the sanctuary is to help the local howler monkey population hurt by the areas growing development. A true sanctuary (no animal touching) which I would recommend (book a visit early in your trip!)

4. Horse riding with @horsejungle for a gentle ride in all of costa rica's gorgeousness! there are many options in the nosara town area including on the beach at sunset though too🐎 🌅 

General info- Be mindful that Costa Rica is considered a developing country, as a tourist you'll be expected to pay US big city prices similar to new york or LA if your staying in Nosara. Unless your cooking yourself this is not a budget-friendly area for food and drinks.
Nosara is 2hr 45min drive from Liberia airport - I would reccomend getting an airport transfer to nosara and then renting locally so you don't have to do a hard drive right after travelling. We used Nosara Transfers who were so reliable and worth the cost!
If you are going to rent a car I think a confident driver+ a compact SUV 4 wheel drive is helpful for exploring as the roads can be a rough ride (we drove through a few deep water filled ravines and steep dirt roads in the hills to get to some places. If you want to do a lot of surfing and yoga you could easily just stay in town with the atv's and tuktuks too though! #nosara #costarica
